public static UVec3 getHeadingAngles(UVec3 v)
Returns the angles of rotation for the orientation of a given vector.

Parameters:
v -
Returns:
UVec3 object where x contains the rotation around the Z axis, and y contains the rotation around the Y axis. The rotations must be performed in the Z-then-Y order.

fromPolar

public static UVec3 fromPolar(float a,
                              float b,
                              float R)
Calculates Cartesian point given a polar coordinate. a=0 is at the <0,-1,0> position, a=PI/2 is at <0,0,1>. b=0 is at the <-1,0,0> position, b=PI/2 is at <0,0,-1>

Parameters:
a - Angle 1
b - Angle 2
R - Radius
Returns:
Vec3 object containing the Cartesian point represented by the polar coordinates.
